WMES Picture Day Oct. 2nd!

WINLOCKSCHOOLS.ORG
WMES Picture Day Oct. 2nd!

post_text:
Bell Studios will be at Winlock Miller Elementary on Friday, October 2nd for individual pictures. To keep families from coming all at one time, we decided to schedule time slots by last name rather than grade level, to minimize crowding.

The main building is still closed to the public. The photographer will be set up in the gym. Families can park in the main parking lot. Please enter the gym through the main gate. Please be sure to maintain social distancing rules and wear facial coverings while waiting your turn and follow signage.

At this time, there will be no picture retakes. Bell Studios will give families an online code for ordering picture packets if desired and will be mailed to families once they have been processed.

Please be sure to follow these time slots:

9:00 - 10:00 A-C

10:00 -11:00 D-G

11:00 -12:00 H-K

12:00 -1:00 L-O

1:00 - 2:00 P-S

2:00 - 3:00 T-Z

post_text:
Ask students about growth mindset. People with a
fixed mindset believe that intelligence and other abilities are fixed -- you either have it or you don’t. People with a growth mindset believe that, through hard work and sustained effort, you can grow your abilities and skills. Research has shown that students with a growth mindset consistently outperform their peers.

post_text: Write about your feelings. Research has shown that even 10 minutes of writing can help reduce anxiety. You can make a worry list, write a diary entry, or start a gratitude journal, where you document things and people for which you are thankful. For kids who are not able to write yet, have them draw a picture and ask them to tell a story about their picture.

post_text:
Good afternoon WMES parents, guardians and community members,

Shortly before 2pm this afternoon (10/3/19), WMES was placed on a partial lockdown (shelter in place) for approximately 40 minutes. The shelter in place procedure was initiated by law enforcement for the protection of the elementary school during an arrest procedure at a nearby residence. Students, staff, and law enforcement effectively executed the drill, and there were no injuries reported during the incident. The safety of our students is of paramount importance. WMES would like to thank law enforcement and the Winlock Police Department for keeping our school/community safe.

post_text:
Dear Winlock Community,

This letter is to update you on the safety incident which occurred today. At approximately 3:00 the Lewis County Sheriff’s Department determined the building to be safe. School will resume tomorrow, October 3rd. The school district and local authorities will continue to work cooperatively on this investigation. We will also be doing whatever we can to ensure these events cease. If you have any information about today’s threat please contact me at 785-3537 or by email at bmaley@winlock.wednet.edu. Thank you for your continued support of Winlock Schools.

Sincerely,
Brian Maley

Winlock School has recently partnered with a revolutionary platform called FINAO, a goals-oriented app created by students, for students, that provides your child a safe, fun and empowering digital community for sharing their educational journey & celebrating them! FINAO is a place for your child to create & journal personal statements of what is important to them and what they aim to achieve – things that matter most to them, their goals & their aspirations. All on their own terms, and by their own definition of success. (You can learn more about FINAO at buff.ly/2MIV6YC)
We also encourage you to join the Winlock FINAO community yourself and use the app to follow your child’s school activities and updates. Feel free to follow your child’s personal journey, as well as any of the groups they are participating in. There’s nothing like being in the know!
